Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.24,0:28:56.48,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“亲爱的博伊德先生，你应该已经得悉”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"Dear Mr Brian Boyd. No doubt by now you have received full information"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.69,0:28:58.10,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“你儿子的死讯”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"about the untimely death of your son."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.18,0:29:00.85,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“说什么也无法减轻您的哀痛”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"No words can ever relieve your grief."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.06,0:29:03.65,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“本部队对他的死深感惋惜，他是个优秀的士兵”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"Our outfiit has felt his loss greatly... He was a fiine soldier"
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.93,0:29:06.90,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“并深信我们所从事的”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"and believed strongly in what we were doing..."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.10,0:29:10.07,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“我们参与了大战中最重要的军事行动”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"We were involved in one of the most important operations of the war."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.27,0:29:12.76,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“艾尔使我们能团结一致”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"Al was the one who held us all together."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.97,0:29:14.56,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“他身先士卒”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"He was the first to volunteer."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.77,0:29:17.79,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“那里有四千人的部队开过”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"We passed a road where over 4,000 troops had passed."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.00,0:29:23.00,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“尊夫尽忠职守”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"Your husband served in a unit whose duty is to place itself beyond..."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.21,0:29:26.08,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“大家都很怀念他”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"...which we all cherish and hold dear..."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.21,0:29:29.88,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“李等人的死对军团打击甚大”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"The loss of Lee and others like him is a distinct blow to the regiment."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.99,0:29:32.99,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“我们了解你想知道”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"We understand your desire to learn about"
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.19,0:29:36.17,画外音,,0000,0000,0000,,“他去世时的情形”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&\fsp0\fscy100%}"the circumstances leading to his death."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.41,0:30:31.38,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,上校，有件事想告诉你\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Colonel, I've got something you should know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.41,0:30:36.47,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,这两人在诺曼第阵亡\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}These two men died in Normandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.68,0:30:40.78,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,这位死于奥哈马海滩     肖恩·瑞恩\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- This one at Omaha Beach.   - "Sean Ryan."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.89,0:30:45.99,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,这位死于犹他     彼得·瑞恩\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- This man at Utah.   - "Peter Ryan."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.17,0:30:52.95,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,这位上周在新几内亚阵亡\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}This man was killed last week in New Guinea.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.04,0:30:58.47,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,丹尼尔·瑞恩\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"Daniel Ryan."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.14,0:31:01.08,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他们是兄弟\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}The three men're brothers,sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.28,0:31:06.34,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他们的妈妈会在下午接到这三封电报\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}I just learned that this afternoon their mother's going to get all three telegrams.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.45,0:31:13.71,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,在抢滩前一晚他们的四弟跟随101空降师\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}There's also a fourth brother who parachuted in with 101st Airborne
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.91,0:31:17.22,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,在诺曼第某处跳伞\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}the night before the invasion. He is somewhere in Normandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.43,0:31:19.79,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他还活着吗     不知道\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Is he alive?   - We don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.72,0:31:25.63,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,跟我来\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.40,0:33:12.13,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,该死\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Goddammit.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.33,0:33:15.79,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,四兄弟都在第29师的同一个连队服役\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}All four were in the same company in the 29th Division
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.00,0:33:22.04,地名,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(960,712)\c&HF3F4FE&}（陆军参谋长马歇尔上将）
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.00,0:33:18.66,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,但苏利文兄弟在朱诺送命后我们便分开了他们\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}but we split them up after the Sullivan brothers died on the Juneau.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.74,0:33:22.04,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,能联络上四弟詹姆斯吗\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Any contact with the fourth son, James?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.24,0:33:27.58,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,不能，他空降在距纽维15里的内陆，深入了敌区\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}No. He was dropped 15 miles inland near Neuville, behind German lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.78,0:33:32.85,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,根本无法知道他空降在哪里\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Mac, there is no way you can know where he was dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.06,0:33:36.99,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,据报101空降师的人失散了\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}First report from lke's people at SHAEF said the 101st is scattered.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.19,0:33:39.32,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,诺曼第有很多被空投错误的部队\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}There are misdrops all over Normandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.53,0:33:43.79,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,就算瑞恩能安然降落也无法找到他\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Assuming Private Ryan even survived the jump, he could be anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.00,0:33:46.09,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,可能他早已阵亡\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}In fact, he's probably K.I.A.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.30,0:33:49.79,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,老实说，若我们派出搜救部队\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}And frankly, if we go sending some sort of rescue mission
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.00,0:33:53.84,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他们就得穿越德军固守区\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}flat hatting throughout German reinforcements along our advance
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.04,0:33:56.94,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,那一定也会阵亡的\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}they're going to be K.I.A., too.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.97,0:34:20.63,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,这里有封信\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}I have a letter here...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.50,0:34:28.53,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,是很久以前给波士顿的比克斯比太太的信，听我读\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}...written a long time ago to a Mrs Bixby in Boston. So bear with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.34,0:34:32.54,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“女士”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"Dear Madam."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.81,0:34:37.87,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“我已从麻萨诸塞州上将副官的”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"I have been shown in the files of the War Department a statement"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.08,0:34:39.85,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“战争部档案得悉”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"of the Adjutant General of Massachusetts"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.05,0:34:43.61,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“你是五位在沙场上”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}'that you are the mother of five..."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.06,0:34:50.09,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“光荣阵亡的战士的母亲”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"...sons who have died gloriously on the field of battle."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.47,0:34:57.16,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“我感到我的言辞薄弱无力”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"I feel how weak and fruitless must be any words of mine"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.37,0:35:00.86,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“根本无法安抚你的悲伤”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"that would attempt to beguile you from the grief"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.07,0:35:04.34,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“也无法弥补你的损失”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"of a loss so overwhelming..."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.54,0:35:10.24,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“但我必须要在此向你致谢”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"...but I can't refrain from tendering the consolation that may be found"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.45,0:35:15.11,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“他们是为了拯救国家而死”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"in the thanks of the republic they died to save."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.89,0:35:23.35,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“愿天主安抚你的丧子之痛”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"May our Heavenly Father assuage the anguish of your bereavement"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.56,0:35:28.76,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“让你永远怀念远去的挚爱”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"and leave you only the cherished memory of the loved and lost"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.97,0:35:32.67,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“神圣的荣耀都归于你们”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"and the solemn pride that must be yours to have laid such a sacrifice"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.87,0:35:38.50,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“因你们为自由付出了重大的代价”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"upon the altar of freedom. Yours very sincerely and respectfully"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.71,0:35:40.91,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“林肯敬上”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"Abraham Lincoln."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.50,0:36:05.18,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,那孩子还活着，我们要派人去找他\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}That boy is alive. We are going to send somebody to find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.14,0:36:10.13,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,然后带他远离战场\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}And we are going to get him the hell out of there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.28,0:36:17.44,地名,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HECF1FD&}（奥哈马海滩，登陆后第三天）
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.75,0:36:26.85,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,后勤官在海滩寻找被炸毁的碉堡\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}The Quartermaster's up the beach a way. Look for a blown-up bunker.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.06,0:36:30.29,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我是C连的米勒     上尉，请进\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Miller,Charlie Company.   - Go on in,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.50,0:36:33.49,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,若六点以前无法卸下坦克的话\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}If we don't off-load the Shermans by 06:00
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.70,0:36:38.57,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,一整师的部队就会被困在卡伦坦\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}we'll have a division stuck at Carentan with its pants around its ankles.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.77,0:36:41.04,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,再说明一下\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Well, you let me know of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.24,0:36:44.51,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,让C连死守维尔维里直到装甲兵开到\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Let Charlie Company hold at Vierville 'til we can get the armour there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.71,0:36:46.34,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,传令兵\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Runner!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.42,0:36:54.24,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,原本空降师该打开缺口的\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Airborne was supposed to win an open door for us
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.24,0:36:56.05,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,但他们却投错地方\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}but misdropped
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.26,0:36:59.09,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,全都失散了，你的情况怎么样\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}and scattered all their sticks into the wind. What's your situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.29,0:37:02.35,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,第四区攻下了\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Yes, sir... Sector Four is secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.56,0:37:09.49,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我们摧毁了这几处的88毫米炮\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}We took out towed 88s here, here and here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.70,0:37:12.47,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,敌军有四部坦克和一些运兵车\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}They got four Shermans and some deuce-and-a-halves.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.67,0:37:15.61,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,这两处的布雷区很大\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}These two minefields are actually one big one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.81,0:37:19.68,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我们到了中心地带，发现地雷的密度很大\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}We went up the middle of it, but it turned into a mixed high-density field.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.88,0:37:22.97,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,什么地雷都有，S44型、S42型\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}A little bit of everything; Sprengmine 44s, Schumne 42s
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.18,0:37:28.52,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,散片型地雷、A-200，连侦测器都无法找到\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}pot mines, A-200s, the little wooden bastard the detectors don't pick up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.72,0:37:31.49,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,这里埋了T43型大地雷\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Here, they placed big mushrooms, Teller mine 43s
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.49,0:37:34.25,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,可能想炸我们的坦克\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}I guess for our tanks
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.46,0:37:37.73,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,从这里到村庄的外围\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}from here right up to the edge of the village, right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.93,0:37:39.96,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,已记下位置，通知了工兵\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}We marked them and called the engineers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.17,0:37:43.66,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,有遇上反抗吗     没想像的那么强\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Resistance?   - We had higher support expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.87,0:37:48.20,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,有一连没配大炮的346步兵\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}There was a company without artillery. Wehrmacht. 346th Infantry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.41,0:37:51.54,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,由卡夫加帕指挥，我们俘虏了23人\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Von Lucke Kampfgruppe. We ended up with 23 prisoners.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.74,0:37:54.21,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,已交由29师的宪兵处置\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}We turned them over to MPs from the 29th.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.52,0:38:00.25,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我军的伤亡呢\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}What about our casualties?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.45,0:38:07.48,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,伤亡人数是35死，70人伤\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Well, the figure is... We're 35 dead, times two wounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.69,0:38:11.65,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他们就是不肯放弃那些重炮\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}They just didn't want to give up those 88s.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.77,0:38:15.46,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,任务很艰巨，所以才找你\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}It was a tough assignment. That was why you got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.67,0:38:18.03,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,是，长官\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.24,0:38:20.17,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,约翰\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}John...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.94,0:38:25.38,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,你又有一项任务了     是，长官\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- I've got another one for you.   - Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.58,0:38:27.74,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,是上级直接交办的\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}It's straight from the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.92,0:38:38.36,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望你和我带一队人到纽维去执行公关任务\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}I wish. You and I are taking a squad to Neuville on a PR mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.56,0:38:40.62,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,由你带队吗\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Oh, are you leading a squad?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.83,0:38:45.09,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,一位二等兵死了三兄弟，所以能回家\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}A private in the 101st lost three brothers and he's got a ticket home.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.30,0:38:47.46,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,为何要去纽维呢     他们觉得他在那里\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Why Neuville?   - They think he's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.67,0:38:50.57,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他是被错投的空降部队之一\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Part of all those Airborne misdrops.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.77,0:38:54.87,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,在战场中找一名士兵很难\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}It won't be easy finding one soldier in the middle of this goddam war.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.07,0:38:57.10,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,就像大海捞针般\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Like finding a needle in a stack of needles.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.31,0:38:58.80,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,那连上兄弟怎么办\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}What about the company?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.01,0:39:02.14,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,最好的跟我们，其他的加入B连\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}We take the pick of the litter, the rest goes to Baker.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.35,0:39:06.41,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊，他们夺走了你的连吗\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Jesus Christ! They took away your company?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.62,0:39:10.72,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,部队是军方的，我们唯有遵命\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}It wasn't mine, it was the Army's. So they told me, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.92,0:39:14.72,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,把莱宾、杰克森、韦德、贝斯里和卡帕佐找来\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Get me Reiben on BAR, Jackson, Wade, Beasley and Caparzo.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.93,0:39:17.95,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,贝斯里死了     那找梅利西吧\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Beasley's dead.   - Alright,Mellish then.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.16,0:39:21.00,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,有人会法语吗     据我所知没有\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Do have a guy who speaks French?   - Not that I know of.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.13,0:39:25.43,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,塔尔博特呢     今早死了\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- What about Talbot?   - This morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.64,0:39:28.70,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我要去找个翻译员\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}I'm going to try and dig up another interpreter.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.91,0:39:31.93,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,到滩头的车辆调度场集合\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Assemble at the battalion motor pool on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.14,0:39:34.58,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,该怎么办     听着，什么\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- What are we going to do?   - Listen up. What?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.78,0:39:36.67,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我要用大块乳酪塞进你的屁股\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Go home wrapped in the American flag
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.67,0:39:38.55,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,好让你棺材盖国旗回家\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}with a hunk of cheese in your ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.75,0:39:41.95,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为你喜欢塞屁股的     什么\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- I thought you liked it in the ass.   - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.15,0:39:44.55,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,立正\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.76,0:39:47.35,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,稍息，我要找提摩西厄本下士\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}As you were. I'm looking for Corporal Timothy Upham.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.56,0:39:49.55,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,是，我就是厄本\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Yes, I'm Upham.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.76,0:39:51.92,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,你会说法语和德语吧     是，长官\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Do you speak French and German?   - Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.13,0:39:54.12,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,有没有口音     法语有\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- How's your accent?   - Slight one in French.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.33,0:39:56.43,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,但德语很纯正     很好\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- My German's clean.   - Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.64,0:40:00.33,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,你已被调派给我了，收拾行囊，我们要到纽维去\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}You've been re-assigned to me. Grab your gear, we're going to Neuville.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.54,0:40:03.98,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,这是什么时候更新的     今天早上八点半\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- When was this updated?   - As of 8:30 this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.18,0:40:07.37,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,这是12SS坦克部队，还有两队人向南推进\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}This is the 12th SS Panzer. These are the two axes advancing south.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.58,0:40:12.57,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,纽维有德军     我知道，下士\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- There are Germans in Neuville.   - I understand, Corporal.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.79,0:40:16.45,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,纽维有很多德军     有问题吗\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- There are a lot of Germans in Neuville.   - You've got a problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.66,0:40:20.15,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我没作战过，只懂绘制地图和翻译\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Please consider that I've never been in combat. I make maps and translate.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.36,0:40:23.56,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我需要会法语和德语的人\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}I need someone who speaks French and German.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.76,0:40:27.86,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,原来的两位阵亡了     我从新兵训练后就没拿过枪\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- My two guys were killed.   - I haven't held a weapon since training.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.07,0:40:30.50,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,基本训练时开过枪吧\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Did you fire the weapon in Basic training?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.70,0:40:34.14,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,开过，长官     那去准备一下\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Yes, sir.   - Well, then get your gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.94,0:40:37.71,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,长官，我能带\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Sir, may I bring...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.91,0:40:44.14,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,能带打字机吗\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}May I bring my typewriter, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.59,0:40:51.35,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,知道了，长官\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.06,0:40:55.82,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.03,0:40:58.12,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,那是纪念品吗     不是\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Is that a souvenir?   - No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.33,0:41:00.09,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,慢慢来\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Take your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.87,0:41:07.43,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,下士，凡事都有好的一面\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}You should look on the bright side of things, Corporal.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.64,0:41:11.80,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,是的     还有，这个也没有用\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Yes.   - For one thing, you don't need those.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.01,0:41:16.07,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,但你需要这个     对，要这个\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- You'll need that.   - Yes. I'll need this, not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.34,0:42:14.50,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,你好     你好\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Hey!   - Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.71,0:42:16.94,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,你是不是想找死\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}You want your head blown off?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.14,0:42:22.01,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,别再用你的爪子碰我，回去你的岗位\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Don't touch me with those rat claws again. Get the fuck back in formation!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.62,0:42:26.02,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是想问你来自哪里\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}I was just wondering where you're from.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.86,0:42:34.62,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,卡帕佐，对吧     滚开，下士\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Caparzo,is it?   - Drop dead,Corporal.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.83,0:42:36.02,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,知道了\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.23,0:42:39.86,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,每次你向上尉敬礼就会惹来德军袭击他\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Every time you salute the Captain,you make him a target for the Germans.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.07,0:42:41.97,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起     帮帮忙，别那么做\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- I'm sorry.   - Do us a favour.Don't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.17,0:42:44.80,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,尤其是当我站在他旁边时，明白吗\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Especially when I'm standing next to him.Capisci?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.00,0:42:48.10,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,明白了     下士，那是什么书\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Capisco.   - Corporal,what's your book about?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.31,0:42:49.60,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,当心你的枪     对不起\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Watch your rifle.   - Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.81,0:42:54.75,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,是关于行军时发展手足之情的方法\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}It's about the brotherhood that develops between soldiers during war.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.95,0:42:58.58,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,手足之情，你懂什么是手足之情\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Brotherhood? What do you know about brotherhood?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.78,0:43:00.81,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,要注意这家伙\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Get a load of this guy, Fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.02,0:43:03.58,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么不去问上尉是哪里人呢\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Why don't you ask the Captain where he's from?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.79,0:43:07.19,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,去问他，他什么都会告诉你的\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Ask the Captain. He'll tell you everything you want to know about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.73,0:43:10.63,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,解释给我听\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Explain the maths of this to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.83,0:43:14.77,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,八个人为什么要冒险救一个人呢\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Where is the sense in risking the lives of the eight of us to save one guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.97,0:43:17.90,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,20度，有人想回答这个问题吗\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}20 degrees. Anybody wants to answer that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.10,0:43:21.20,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,莱宾，想想那可怜虫的妈妈吧\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Reiben, think about the poor bastard's mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.41,0:43:23.53,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,医护兵，我也有妈妈\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Hey, Doc, I've got a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.74,0:43:26.07,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,你有妈妈，中士也有妈妈\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}You've got a mother, Sarge has got a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.28,0:43:29.77,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我敢说上尉也有妈妈\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Shit, I bet even the Captain's got a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.98,0:43:32.75,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,也许上尉没有，但我们全都有\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Maybe not the Captain, but the rest of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.95,0:43:35.25,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“不问原因，只求为国牺牲”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"Their's is not to reason why their's is but to do and die"
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.45,0:43:39.75,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,下士，那是什么意思\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}What the fuck is that supposed to mean, Corporal?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.96,0:43:41.29,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都该死吗\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}We're all supposed to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.49,0:43:45.16,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,厄本说的是我们的职责     是，长官\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Upham's talking about our duty.   - Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.36,0:43:46.39,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我们全都得服从命令\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}We all have orders to follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.80,0:43:53.70,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,是的，长官，谢谢    就算任务是“苦差”也要吗\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Yes, sir. Thank you. Even if the mission is "FUBAR"?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.91,0:43:56.40,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,这才更加要服从\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Especially if the mission is "FUBAR".
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.08,0:44:00.81,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“苦差”是什么     那是德语\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- What's "FUBAR"?   - It's German.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.01,0:44:03.14,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,没听过\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Never heard of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.35,0:44:07.48,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,长官，我对此有点意见\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Sir, I have an opinion on this matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.69,0:44:10.38,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,说出来听听吧\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}By all means, share it with the squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.59,0:44:12.82,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我的想法是\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}From my way of thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.03,0:44:17.79,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,这次任务浪费了宝贵的军事资源\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}this mission is a misallocation of valuable military resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.00,0:44:19.83,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,是吗，继续\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Yeah? Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.03,0:44:25.63,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得上帝赐给我打仗的天分\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}It seems to me that God gave me a sepcial gift made me a fine instrument of warfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.84,0:44:29.67,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,莱宾，听好，这样抱怨才对，继续，杰克森\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Reiben,pay attention.Now, this is the way to gripe.Continue,Jackson.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.88,0:44:35.31,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,要是他派我这个狙击手\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}If He was to put me and this sniper rifle anywhere up to and including
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.51,0:44:38.71,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,到希特勒一里范围内\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}one mile of Adolf Hitler with a clear line of sight, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.92,0:44:42.15,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,大家就能收拾行囊回家，战争就结束了，阿门\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Pack your bags, fellas, the war is over. Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.35,0:44:44.58,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,乡巴佬，这主意不错\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}That's brilliant, bumpkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.79,0:44:47.62,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,上尉，你呢，你不会抱怨吗\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}What about you, Captain? You don't gripe at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.83,0:44:51.09,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我是上尉，身负重任，不会向你抱怨\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}I don't gripe to you. I'm a captain. There's a chain of command.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.30,0:44:53.09,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,上级永远是发牢骚的对象\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Gripe always go up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.30,0:44:58.10,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,你向我发牢骚，我向我上级发牢骚，如此类推\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}You gripe to me, I gripe to my superior officers, and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.30,0:45:02.17,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会在你面前发牢骚，你是突击队员，应该明白\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}I don't gripe in front of you. You should know that as a Ranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.37,0:45:07.04,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起，就当你不是上尉或我是少校吧\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}I'm sorry, but let's say that you weren't a captain or that I was a major.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.25,0:45:08.98,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,你会说什么\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}What would you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.18,0:45:13.08,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,那样我就会说，这项任务棒极了\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}In that case, I'd say, "This is an excellent mission"
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.29,0:45:17.72,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,意义重大，值得我全力以赴\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"with a valuable objective worthy of my best efforts."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.92,0:45:23.49,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,而且我对瑞恩的母亲感到深切的悲痛\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"Moreover, I feel heartfelt sorrow for the mother of Private Ryan"
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.70,0:45:28.96,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,为了慰藉她，我愿意赔上我与部下的性命\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"and I'll lay down my life and those of my men, especially yours, Reiben"
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.17,0:45:30.66,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,尤其是你，莱宾\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"to ease her suffering."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.04,0:45:34.40,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他很棒     我喜欢他\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- He's good.   - I love him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.85,0:45:46.65,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,算了\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.89,0:46:31.02,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,打雷     闪电\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Thunder!   - Flash!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.23,0:46:35.03,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,厄本，到那边去，莱宾，你们四个过去\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Upham, over there. Reiben, you four go.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.94,0:46:45.81,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,去吧\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Go, go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.38,0:46:54.32,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,很高兴看见你     希尔中士，救星来了\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- You are a sight for sore eyes.   - Sergeant Hill, our reliefs showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.52,0:46:58.62,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,有多少人     八个，但不是救兵\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- How many are you?   - Eight. We're not your relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.82,0:47:02.09,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么     我们来找二等兵瑞恩\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- What do you mean, sir?   - We're here for a Private Ryan.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.29,0:47:04.73,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,谁     瑞恩，为什么\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Who?   - Ryan? What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.00,0:47:08.23,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他在这里吗     大概在镇的另一边\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Is he here?   - Maybe on the other side of the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.43,0:47:10.93,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,周围都有德军，很难通过\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}It's hard to get to. The Germans punched a hole in our centre.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.14,0:47:14.07,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我军给德军切断，他叫什么名字\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- They cut us right in two.   - What's his name,again?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.27,0:47:17.37,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞恩，詹姆斯·瑞恩，隶属101空降师\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Ryan, James Ryan. He dropped in with the 101st.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.58,0:47:20.60,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,高德曼，找传令兵来     传令兵\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Goldman, get me a runner!   - Runner!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.81,0:47:22.71,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.42,0:47:28.82,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,琼斯，让开\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Jonesy, make a hole up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.49,0:47:33.42,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我们被东面的炮火所阻\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}We got stopped by fire from the eastward.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.63,0:47:37.25,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,德军聚集了两个团的兵力\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}The Germans have been reinforcing two regiments all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.46,0:47:39.52,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,已经有四十五分钟没有动静\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}It's been quiet for 45 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.73,0:47:42.17,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,德军正把火力集中于西面\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}The Germans concentrate their fire westward.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.37,0:47:45.67,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,谁在广播     达伍德·迪·撒多夫\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Who's that on the loudspeaker?   - Dagwood Duesseldorf.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.87,0:47:50.37,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他在替德军激励士气\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Our friendly neighbourhood morale officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.58,0:47:53.84,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,“自由神像完蛋了”\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}"The Statue of Liberty is kaput."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.05,0:47:56.41,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,想扰乱我们军心\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}That's disconcerting.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.89,0:48:05.12,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,笨蛋，你父亲的包皮已被割掉了\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Your father was circumcised by my rabbi, you prick!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.46,0:48:09.98,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,开枪掩护\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Cover!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.90,0:48:18.60,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,去吧\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.73,0:48:44.46,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,去你的臭混蛋     伏下\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- You sadistic fucking animals!   - Get down.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.66,0:48:47.53,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,敌人知道我军通讯中断，所以针对传令兵\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}They know we're not in direct contact. They'll single out the runners.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.73,0:48:49.29,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么要射杀他们\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Why do they shoot them up?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.50,0:48:53.06,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,不能留活口，以防军情外泄，我们也会这样做\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}As long as his lungs are working, he carries the message. We'd do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.27,0:48:56.80,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,不，我们不会     韦德，准备起程\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- No, we wouldn't!   - Wade! Get them ready to travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.01,0:48:58.84,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,博伊德     来吧\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Boyd!   - Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.04,0:49:01.71,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,再试一遍，设法通知汉米尔上尉我们正赶过去\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Try again! Let Captain Hamill know we're coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.91,0:49:04.18,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,纽维其他地方怎么样\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}What's the rest of Neuville like?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.38,0:49:08.18,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,接着会看到两层建筑物，有很多窗户\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}The next block's got two-storey buildings. A lot of windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.39,0:49:10.45,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,有一广场可作藏身之用\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}There's a square with good cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.66,0:49:13.06,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,带我去，中士，留在这里\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Show me. Sarge, hold right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.26,0:49:14.69,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,是，长官\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.93,0:49:21.49,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,别在这里挨打，到里面躲避\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Stay out of this enfilade and use the buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.70,0:49:24.64,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,到左边去，边走边射击，我们各派两人\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Try a left hook. Shoot and scoot. Two of yours, two of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.84,0:49:27.33,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,黑斯亭斯、高德曼，到前面去\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Hastings, Goldman! Up front!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.47,0:49:31.14,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,莱宾、卡帕佐     通讯仍受敌军干扰\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Reiben, Caparzo.   - They're still jamming us.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.34,0:49:34.40,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,尽快到角落去，小心行事\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Short runs, high and low at the corners. It's going to be tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.61,0:49:36.98,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,准备进行近身战，去吧\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Be prepared for close contact. Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.18,0:49:39.65,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,厄本，跟霍瓦特中士待在一起\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Upham! You stay with Sergeant Horvath.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.85,0:49:43.88,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,上尉，我会像内裤般粘着他\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Stay here! I'll wear him like underwear, Captain. You stay with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.53,0:49:54.97,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,广场闸口在大楼的尽头\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Past the end of the block are the gates of the square.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.17,0:49:57.14,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,好     好的\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Good.   - Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.51,0:50:06.24,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,莱宾，上尉从哪里来的\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Reiben, where's the Captain from?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.45,0:50:10.18,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,猜中的话有奖     奖金三百块\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- If you figure it out, you'll get a prize.   - 300 bucks, last I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.38,0:50:13.87,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,大家下注，最少五块\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}The company's got a pool. Five bucks gets you in.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.93,0:50:24.45,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,就在拐弯处，躲到闸门后面去\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}It's around this corner. Defilade right up to those gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.00,0:50:28.30,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,一定有人知道他来自哪里\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Somebody must know where he's from.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.50,0:50:31.47,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我跟他一起那么久也毫无头绪\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}I've been with him since Casserene Pass. I don't have a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.67,0:50:36.51,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我的脚踝很痛，战争没结束已经要坐轮椅\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}My ankles are killing me. I'll need a wheelchair before the war is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.71,0:50:40.97,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,老天，就跟老妇一样\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}That's it! Oh, my God! That ankle is like an old woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.18,0:50:44.55,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,就像，老天\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Like an old... Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.85,0:50:49.08,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,莱宾，你连他上哪所学校也不知道吗\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Reiben. So you don't even know where he went to school?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.29,0:50:53.52,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他没念书，是军部用大兵尸体组装而成\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}He didn't go to school. They assembled him at OCS out of dead Gls.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.73,0:50:57.06,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道他的来历\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Pay attention to detail. I know where he's from and what he did
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.26,0:50:59.36,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我看得仔细\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}because I pay attention to detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.57,0:51:02.83,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,厄本，别信他的鬼话\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Hey, Upham! Careful you don't step in the bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.37,0:51:10.64,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,说吧     打雷\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Do it.   - Thunder!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.84,0:51:13.37,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,打雷，不然开火\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Thunder, or we will fire on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.58,0:51:16.57,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,梅利西、卡帕佐，过来\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Mellish, Caparzo, come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.39,0:51:26.22,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,叫他们表明身分\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Tell them to show themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.10,0:51:40.80,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,问问德军在哪里\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Ask them where the Germans are.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.34,0:51:47.51,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他说什么     关于孩子的\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- What is he saying?   - Something about the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.71,0:51:49.87,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,孩子     他想我们带走孩子\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Kids?   - He wants us to take them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.08,0:51:51.81,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,不行，不能带走孩子\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}No, no. We can't take the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.02,0:51:57.51,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,不可以，不行\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}We can't take the kids! No, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.73,0:52:02.69,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他们以为这样较安全     才不会\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- They think they'll be safe.   - They won't be safe with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.20,0:52:06.66,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,你疯了吗，听从上尉的命令\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Are you nuts? Listen to the Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.27,0:52:09.17,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,他们以为孩子会安全一点\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}They think they'll be safe with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.37,0:52:14.81,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,什么地方也不会安全，卡帕佐，交回孩子\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}It's not safe anywhere. Caparzo! Put that kid back!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.58,0:52:19.51,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,卡帕佐，把孩子还给他们     请放心\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Caparzo, put the girl back!   - It's OK, it's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.71,0:52:21.87,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,交回孩子\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Give that kid back!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.05,0:52:26.78,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,厄本，怎么说请放心     她让我想起外甥女\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}- Upham, how do you say, "It's OK?" I can't.   - She reminds me of my niece.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.99,0:52:28.92,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,把孩子交回去\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Get the kid back up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.12,0:52:32.52,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,最少也该把她带到下个市镇\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}We should at least take her to the next town.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.76,0:52:35.82,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,我们有任务在身，不是来救孩子\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}We're not here to do that, we're here to follow orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.03,0:52:39.16,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,中士，把孩子接过来\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Sarge, take this goddam kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.36,0:52:42.03,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,躲好\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Cover, cover!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.54,0:52:50.74,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,糟糕\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.94,0:52:52.84,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,可恶，哪里射过来的\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}Goddammit! Where did that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.51,0:52:58.61,对白,,0000,0000,0000,,听到枪声前他已倒地\N{\fs49\fnWin7 YaHei\shad2\c&H849F7F&}He was on the ground before we heard the shot.
